Or dotes you eite an endless chain From Inachus to Codrus’ reign, Thot sels-devoted king who fell

A martyr to his country’s weal; And then you prate, Ο Telephus, About the raee of AEoeus,

But of the priee we pay for wine

Who the warm bath may hesi prepare, Or shield us from the nipping nir

Cournge, my friend! drink fair, fill up One bumper in the brimming oup

To the new moon's returning light, Another to the dark midnight,

A third to greet the rising morn
